Bethmara Kessler 








 
Bethmara Kessler

			Senior Vice President, Integrated Global Services
Bethmara Kessler was named Senior Vice President-Integrated Global Services (IGS) in November 2016. She reports to Denise Morrison, President and Chief Executive Officer, and she is a member of the Campbell Leadership Team.
Bethmara leads Campbell’s global shared services organization in creating value, fueling growth, and transforming the way Campbell works. IGS is designed around eight operational functions that provide transactional to knowledge-based services from more than 25 locations around the world.
Bethmara joined Campbell as Vice President, Corporate Audit, in 2014 and she was named Vice President-Strategy and Operations, Integrated Global Services, in September 2016.
Previously, she had served as Senior Vice President, Internal Audit, and Co-Chief Compliance Officer at Warner Music Group.
Before that, she co-founded and worked for the Fraud and Risk Advisory Group, a firm that specialized in the delivery of management consulting services for global clients. She also served on the executive leadership team at Limited Brands, where she was a key member of the team that created the company’s shared services organization, and she created its continuous improvement capability.
Bethmara earned her bachelor of business administration degree in accounting from Bernard M. Baruch College. She is a certified fraud examiner and a certified information systems auditor. She is a member of the Association of Fraud Examiners, Institute of Internal Auditors and Information Systems Audit & Control Association.
She was named among the Top 100 Leading Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender (LGBT) Executives by the Financial Times, in partnership with OUTstanding, a LGBT network, in 2015 and 2016, and among the NJ BIZ Best Fifty Women in Business for 2017.





