Speakers





Bethmara Kessler

                VP Audit
            
Campbell Soup



Bethmara joined Campbell as Vice President, Corporate Audit in July 2014. She joined Campbell from Warner Music Group, where she served as Senior Vice President, Internal Audit and Co-Chief Compliance Officer. 
Prior to Warner Music Group, Bethmara served as the Managing Director of the Fraud and Risk Advisory Group and the SVP, Enterprise Business Risk Management for LBrands. Bethmara has had other roles serving as the head of audit for EMI Group, Plc and has worked in various capacities at companies such as Avon Products, Nabisco and Ernst & Young.
Bethmara graduated with her bachelor of business administration degree in accounting from Bernard M. Baruch College in New York. She is a certified fraud examiner and a certified information systems auditor.
Bethmara serves on the faculty and advisory council of the Association of Fraud Examiners (ACFE). She delivers training for the ACFE and other professional organizations on a variety of topics related to fraud prevention and detection, investigations, auditing, compliance and risk.
Bethmara and her wife Lynne reside in Philadelphia, PA.

