Home > Newsroom > Bethmara Kessler is One of New Jersey’s Best 50 Women in Business			









Mar 20, 2017Mar 28, 2017 | News 
Bethmara Kessler is One of New Jersey’s Best 50 Women in Business




Share on Facebook 



 




NJBIZ Magazine has recognized our own Bethmara Kessler, Senior Vice President-Integrated Global Services, among its Best Fifty Women in Business for 2017. The award honors New Jersey’s most dynamic business women who are making headlines in their field.
 

 
Since joining Campbell nearly three years ago, Bethmara has led change and major transformation, built capability across businesses, fostered a culture of continuous improvement, mentored and developed top talent and inspired us to think differently.
 
Bethmara is the executive sponsor of our OPEN employee network, and beyond her support of the LGBT community, she is fully committed to Workplace Diversity and Inclusion initiatives.
 
CEO Denise Morrison says, “I admire her passion, creativity, and energy, and her ability to collaborate to drive business improvement. I was proud to nominate Bethmara for this award.”




